      "review_summary": "The branch changes Telegram routing and auto-reply dispatch so plugin-owned runtime bindings can claim Telegram forum topic messages under `message_tool_only`, adds focused tests, and also includes broad unrelated formatting/generated-file changes.\n\nReproducibility: yes. A high-confidence source path exists: bind a Telegram forum topic to a plugin-owned runtime binding, set visible replies to `message_tool_only`, and send a normal unmentioned topic message; current dispatch skips the plugin claim under that suppression while the PR body provides after-fix live logs.",
